text: Unfortunately, entropy dictates resurrection of decayed lifeforms is impossible. Just like paper, once crumpled, cannot be made perfectly flat & straight, nor can paper burned be unburned, in both examples due to entropy, neither can the decayed remains of a living thing be made whole again. The creature, just like the wrinkled paper sheet, or pile of ashes, would be a shadow of its former self--a zombie-like thing. The movie alludes to it, but goes further and says that resurrected creatures would be both less and more than what they were before death. But of course we know that they can't possibly be more, due to entropy. Still, it's a fun concept that could be entertaining, from a make believe perspective, assuming they nail the execution...

text: This is a *Dumb Movie* and I‚Äôll tell you why  So the premise of the movie is that a group of scientist have found a way to bring people back from the dead. However when the person is brought back to life, a demon attaches itself to the soul and brought to earth with the person or creature. My question is, what is the purpose of the demon going on a mindless killing spree?  Think about it for a moment, humans, have found means to bring demons to the mortal plane. Better yet, the person in charge of such an operation has been brought back to life with a demon attached. Now with this set up, wouldn‚Äôt it be smarter if the demon instead were to lie and wait, plant messages into her mind to use the Lazarus more and more, bringing more people back to life, bringing along more demons until finally you‚Äôre given the opportunity to bring back someone important or powerful like, a President or a Prime Minister with a demon attached to them?  Nope, apparently, demons with supernatural powers are apparently so dumb, the second they get the chance they just want to kill people for the hell of it. This movie is basically like The Purge; a *GREAT* idea with such a boundless premise, able to take the movie into nearly any crazy and unforeseeable way imaginable, and its basically turned into a worthless slasher/killing flick, but with demonic powers. I‚Äôve lost faith in humanity already but I swear if this movie blows up at the box office‚Ä¶¬†
